title: Prince - For Those Of You On Valium (Live 1987)
description:
PRINCE - FOR THOSE OF YOU ON VALIUM (LIVE, 1987)

As I was rummaging thru some piles of ancient CDs I have, I came across this 
Prince concert video. It was a great throwback to the time when Prince was 
all kinds of AWSUM instead of a gone-bonkers has-been who makes mediocre
crap. I think I got it from a friend who had got it from some peer-to-peer 
network or another about 15 years ago. It MUST be old as dirt, as the video 
codec is DIVX 3. The only thing I did to the original video was building the 
missing index, otherwise it's presented as is.
 
http://thedigitalgarden.org/0-9/261-4-those-of-you-on-valium.html

Quote:

"Sign O' The Times Tour Warm Up Show

First Avenue, Minneapolis

21st March 1987

1. Introduction  
2. Housequake   
3. Girls And Boys  
4. Slow Love   
5. Hot Thing 
6. Now's The Time  
7. Sheila E Drum Solo   
8. Strange Relationship  
9. Forever In My Life   
10. Kiss   
11. It's Gonna Be A Beautiful Night

[...]The title comes from a line Prince says at the opening of the show, 
'For those of you on Valium, my name is Prince.' This is a Live warm-up show at 
First Ave for the Sign O The Times tour. The source for this recording is a well 
circulated video tape. The show is excellent, Prince is loose and having fun."
